getNthServiceNode

protected Node getNthServiceNode(Set<Node> clusterNodes,
                                 int n)
                          throws IncompleteClusterException
Get the n'th node from the given cluster nodes that have the service.

Parameters:
clusterNodes - Nodes in the cluster.
n - number of the node with the service on it.
Returns:
N'th node on the cluster with the given service.
Throws:
IncompleteClusterException - if there are not fewer than n + 1 nodes with the service

getServiceInstanceNum

protected int getServiceInstanceNum(Node node,
                                    List<Node> sortedNodeList)
Get the instance number of the node. For example, suppose there are 3 nodes with zookeeper with node numbers 3, 7, and 17. The instance num of the node with node number 3 is 1, the instance num of the node with node number 7 is 2, and the instance num of the node with node number 17 is 3.

Parameters:
node - Node to find the instance number for.
sortedNodeList - List of nodes with the service on it, sorted by node number.
Returns:
Instance number of the node.
